Business Brief -- Exxon Corp.:
   Gasoline Price-Fixing Case
   Is Settled for $9.9 Million
The four states alleged that Exxon and six other oil
companies conspired to raise gasoline prices and eliminate
competition. The states are continuing their cases against
Chevron Corp., Mobil Corp., the Shell Oil Co. subsidiary of
Royal Dutch/Shell Group, Texaco Inc., Unocal Corp. and
Atlantic Richfield Co.